Peru Stocks: La Cima, Buenaventura, Minera IRL, Atacocha, Volcan

-- B y   A l e x   E m e r y
-- 
2011-03-21T20:44:39Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-21/peru-stocks-la-cima-buenaventura-minera-irl-atacocha-volcan.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses
and share prices are as of 4:11 p.m.  New York  time.  The  Lima  General Index surged 4.3 percent to 21,375.17. The
MSCI All Peru Capped Index rose 1.2 percent to 2,901.72.  Miners gained after  Gold Fields Ltd. (GFI)  offered to buy the
remaining shares of its Peruvian subsidiary, spurring sellers to
invest the proceeds in other stocks, said Javier Frisancho, a
trader at Lima-based brokerage Kallpa Securities SAB.  Gold Fields La Cima SA (LACIMAI1 PE) jumped 36 percent to
4.20 soles, the purchase price offered by Gold Fields on March
18 for an 8 percent stake in its local unit. Cia. de Minas
Buenaventura SAA (BVN PE), the country’s biggest precious-metals
miner, rose 4.1 percent to $44 after gold climbed for a fourth
straight session in New York.  Minera IRL Ltd. (MIRL)  , a U.K.
minerals explorer with a gold mine in Peru, gained 3.5 percent
to $1.50.  Silver and tin miners rose after the metals advanced in
 London .  Cia. Minera Atacocha SA (ATACOBC1 PE), the Lima-based
silver and zinc producer, surged 9 percent to 1.21 soles.  Minsur
SA (MINSURI1)  (MINSURI1 PE), the world’s fourth-largest tin producer,
gained 5.5 percent to 4.20 soles. Volcan Cia. Minera SAA
(VOLCABC1 PE), Peru’s biggest silver producer, rose for the
first session in 11, gaining 5.3 percent to 3.80 soles.  Fuel refiners gained after crude oil advanced in New York
on concern that escalating turmoil in the Middle East may
curtail shipments.  Refineria la Pampilla SA (RELAPAC1 PE), a unit of  Spain ’s
Repsol YPF SA, rose 5 percent to 1.89 soles.  Maple Energy Plc. (MPLE) 
, the oil and natural gas producer with operations in
Peru, gained 4.3 percent to 97 cents.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Alex Emery  in Lima at 
 aemery1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
 papadopoulos@bloomberg.net  